We recommended to the management to:
Direct the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Engineer to coordinate as to the determination of the cost of ongoing projects as of year-end;
Require the Municipal Engineer to submit to the Municipal Accountant’s Office a copy of the Consolidated Report on Government Projects/Programs/Activities (PPAs) for the fourth quarter as a reference for the status of ongoing and completed projects implemented by the LGU;
Require the Municipal Engineer to submit to the Municipal Accountant’s Office a copy of the Statement of Work Accomplishment (SWA) for ongoing projects with unrecorded work accomplishments;
Submit a copy of the Journal Entry Voucher (JEV) reflecting the year-end adjusting entries (if any) made together with the working paper and relevant supporting documents such as the Statement of Work Accomplishment (SWA) to the COA Office for verification.

We recommended to the management to instruct the Office of the Municipal Accountant to do the following in the Trust Fund books of accounts:
To record the income account “Transfers from General Fund of Unspent DRRMF” for all funds receive related to the unspent DRRMF;
To record the expenditure accounts with sub-subsidiary ledger expense accounts for each Program, Projects and Activities (PPA) approved by the Council for all actual expenses related to the unspent appropriation of LDRRMF  ;
To prepare the working papers in the determination of the remaining balance of the account “Trust Liability – LDRRM” as of the end of December 31, 2021;
Once determined, set up an adjusting entry thereof to recognize the income account
These recordings conform to the Local Government Chart of Accounts under IPSAS.  Once followed, the monitoring of balances between actual payments and allocated amount for each program, project and activity as approved by the Council could be done at all times. Consequently, the preparation of the required Statement of Financial Performance under Trust Fund books could already be done.

We recommended to the management to:
Refrain from paying to its officials and employees those allowances, incentives and other fringe benefits not covered by existing appropriations and, consequently, have no legal basis. Further payments may lead to audit disallowances as provided under COA Circular No. 2013-003 dated January 30, 2013;
Provide proper appropriations and guidelines in case the management decides to continue the grant “Load Allowances” to its officials and employees.

We recommended to the Municipal Mayor to require the HRMO and MHO (if warranted) to implement the following courses of actions to establish the eligibility of the personnel granted with AHDP and SRA worth ₱ 2,206,170.73 as follows
Require all the payees to submit their individual accomplishments reports signed by their supervisor(s) indicating that they directly catered to or were in contact with COVID-19 patients, persons under investigation, or persons under monitoring. The same should indicate their area of assignment;
To confirm the Certification rendered by the MHO on the number of days  the payees rendered actual service;
Require the health workers, including the BHWs, to submit copies of their certifications that they are indeed accredited and registered under the local health board; and
Attached copies of submitted reports to DOH-CHD (Center of Health Developments) on the number of the COVId-19 patients attended to as required in Section 6.4.b of DBM-DOH Joint Circulars Nos 1 and 2, both dated November 25, 2020.

We recommended to the management to:

•	Strictly adhere to the provisions of the NGAS Manual;
•	Require the accountant to stop the practice of recording/charging regular purchases of drugs and medicines immediately to the expense accounts and should maintain on a current basis in the General Ledger (GL) and Inventory Account all purchases of drugs and medicines for stock, regardless of whether or not they are consumed within the accounting period. Issuance thereof shall be recorded based on the Report of Drugs and Medicines Issued;
•	Require the accountant to maintain and update regularly the Ledger Card for each inventory stock which shall contain the details of the GL accounts and to reconcile their cards/records regularly with that of the Municipal Health Office; and
•	Designate a General Services Officer (GSO) and to conduct an inventory of supplies and materials annually, prepare a Report on the Physical Count of Inventories by type of inventory as of given date, prepare on a monthly basis Report on Supplies and Materials Issued (RSMI) based in the Requisition and Issue Slips, and maintain Stock Cards for inventories and reconciled with the records of the Accounting Office regularly.

